, proximal width (DTP) = 
<quantity box="[254,357,1996,2020]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.01" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="30.1">30.1 mm</quantity>
, distal depth (
<collectionCode box="[516,597,1996,2020]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">DAPD</collectionCode>
; estimated at epiphyseal line) = 
<quantity box="[963,1066,1996,2020]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.31" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="13.1">13.1 mm</quantity>
, distal width (DTD; estimated at epiphyseal line) = 
<quantity box="[360,442,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 mm</quantity>
. The distal diameters are confirmed by referred distal metacarpal 
<collectionCode box="[1183,1247,152,176]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/47nz-wbm0" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">RGM</collectionCode>
<number box="[1254,1350,151,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="261.53">261.530</number>
: 
